&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Most modern radios can store these as memory channels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Always verify the tone (PL/CTCSS) is correct before transmitting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Standard offsets: 2m uses +/- 0.600 MHz, 70cm uses +/- 5.000 MHz&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Negative offset (-) means transmit frequency is lower than receive&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
